body:
Bundles with different field names dedup, but they don't if the bundle is an element of a vector.
The `Simple0` and `Simple1` should dedup.
```
firrtl.circuit "Simple" {
  firrtl.module @Simple0() {
    %a = firrtl.wire: !firrtl.vector<bundle<a: uint<1>>, 2>
  }
  firrtl.module @Simple1() {
    %b = firrtl.wire: !firrtl.vector<bundle<b: uint<1>>, 2>
  }
  firrtl.module @Simple() {
    firrtl.instance simple0 @Simple0()
    firrtl.instance simple1 @Simple1()
  }
}
```
